Analysing de distribution of Ringlet butterfly in the UK
We analysed the distribution of the Ringlet butterfly (Aphantopus hyperantus) using \(&gt;\) 2 million records from 140,887 unique 1 km\(^2\) from the BNM programme between 1970 and 2014.

Occupancy model framework where

\[
\begin{aligned}
y_{ijt} = \begin{cases} 1 & \text{if Ringlet is on checklist } i \text{ on visit } j \text{ during year } t\\ 0 & \text{any species other than Ringlet is recorded}\end{cases}
\end{aligned}
\]
